{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix double-free issue in RLC entity reassembly functions\n\n### Summary\nA double-free vulnerability exists in the RLC layer reassembly functions for both UM and AM entities. The issue manifests when processing SDUs that span multiple PDUs. During reassembly, the `reassemble_and_deliver` functions in both entities directly call `free(pdu->data)` to release PDU payload memory, but the same PDU structs remain in the reception list and are later passed to `nr_rlc_free_pdu()` which also attempts to free the same data pointer.\n\nThis leads to heap corruption and potential crashes during heavy RLC traffic scenarios. The problem was observed during stress testing with high PDU segmentation rates.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/nr_rlc/nr_rlc_entity_um.c`: Modified `reassemble_and_deliver` to mark PDUs as processed by setting `pdu->data = NULL` instead of directly freeing the data\n- `openair2/LAYER2/nr_rlc/nr_rlc_entity_am.c`: Applied identical fix to AM entity's `reassemble_and_deliver` function  \n- `openair2/LAYER2/nr_rlc/nr_rlc_pdu.c`: Added NULL check in `nr_rlc_free_pdu` to safely handle already-processed PDUs\n\n"
}